==English==
[[Image:Liocarcinus vernalis.jpg|thumb|A crab]]
===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|krăb}}, {{IPA|/kræb}}, {{SAMPA|/kr{b/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æb|-æb]]

===Etymology 1===
{{ME.}} ''[[crabbe]]'', from {{OE.}} ''[[crabba]]''

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[crustacean]] of the [[infraorder]] ''[[Brachyura]]'', having five pairs of legs, the [[foremost]] of which are in the form of [[claw]]s, and a [[carapace]].
# A [[bad-tempered]] person.
# (''in plural'' '''crabs'''; ''informal'') An [[infestation]] of [[pubic lice]].
#{{rfv-sense}} {{UK}} {{slang}} a [[twenty-pence piece]] (so named because they are seven-sided and because of the [[urban myth]] that crabs have a seventh [[leg]] they keep inside their [[shell]] for [[emergency|emergencies]]).

